<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-10T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-10T18:00:00-05:00" n="321" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d321">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 Belgium/224a: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-10T18:00:00-05:00">March
                                        10, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>10. Department’s instruction No. 320, February 4, 1936.<note n="5" xml:id="d321fn5">See footnote 2, <ref target="#pg_407">p.
                                        407</ref>.</note> Belgian Ambassador appears to be favorably
                                impressed by our arguments for cooperation to suppress alcohol
                                smuggling and stated that he is planning an approach to his
                                Government which he hopes will be successful in obtaining action we
                                desire. He asks that in the meantime we make no further direct
                                efforts ourselves.</p>
                            <pb facs="0491" n="411" xml:id="pg_411"/>
                            <p>Please disregard, therefore, the request in our instruction No. 332
                                of March 10 to do whatever you can to facilitate the Ambassador’s
                                efforts, and omit any further reference to this subject for the
                                present in your relations with the Belgian Government.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>